         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <bioghist id="aspace_9b5ad5db1b769fdcf76cc1f3b5afb1f8">
         <head>TRISTAN KLINGSOR, 1874-1966</head>
         <p>Tristan Klingsor (born Léon Leclère), was a poet, painter and musician, known for his collaborations with Maurice Ravel.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_6b8e7efde43c8429423983969c8eacdc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This group of material contains a notebook, a holograph page of a work by Klingsor, letters to Klingsor, drafts of letters by Klingsor, financial papers, photographs, and other personal papers.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
